 Find the remainder of \[p(x)=1+x^2+x^4+\cdots+x^{22}\]divided by \[q(x)=1+x+x^2+\cdots+x^{11}.\] We have \begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{x^{24}-1}{x^2-1} \\ &= q(x)(x^{10}-x^8+x^6-x^4+x^2)+127.
\end{align*}Thus the remainder is $\boxed{127.}$ </think> <answer> 127 </answer>

